Dear Ed Pegg Jr,

=20

After some oral discussion with Adriaan van Oosterom,  I send you an
attachment

containing a slightly revised version, SolidVersionR of your original
procedure

SolidVersion. Happily to say, this version works quite well, also for =
the
regular terahedron.

=20

In the first place I did away with the triangle argument as this may =
lead to
some

confusion for possible applications. In the second place I used =
ArcTan[x,y]
instead

of ArcTan[z]. Finally I wrapped N[] around the denominator of the =
expression
you

used, otherwise one ends up with an integer representation since=20

Vertices [Tetrahedron] returns with integer representations of the =
vertices

=20

As van Oosterom already pointed out, the rotation of the sides of the
tetrahedron

should be kept in mind. The rotation sense can be obtained from calling =
( I
used to

work with Fortran) Faces [Tetrahedron].

One now obtains for the sum of the four solid angles a numerical
representation

of 12 =B4 ZXp as indeed should be.

=20

I highly appreciated the way the original formula is programmed. This
appoach

is far outside my ken, since I am only a self taught man in Mathematica  =


=20

Kindly yours,=20

Jan Strackee

=20
Prof.Dr.J.Strackee

=20
Portengen 8

